<paragraph id="8BB23F60DC67FFE3F562366FFBD9F995" blockId="10.[347,1097,1536,1558]" box="[347,1097,1536,1558]" pageId="10" pageNumber="787">
D e s c r i p t i o n: 2.0- 
<quantity id="4CF59285DC67FFE3F65F366EFD27F995" box="[614,695,1536,1558]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="10" pageNumber="787" unit="mm" value="2.7">2.7 mm</quantity>
. Coloration: body uniformly yellowish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB23F60DC67FFE3F5623648FD2CF932" blockId="10.[347,1255,1574,1713]" pageId="10" pageNumber="787">
Head approximately as wide as long; puncturation extremely fine, barely noticeable; surface with shallow or very shallow microreticulation and with some shine. Eyes strongly reduced (
<figureCitation id="133623E5DC67FFE3F620360EFDF8F9F5" box="[537,616,1632,1654]" captionStart="Figs 36-42" captionStartId="11.[347,387,1604,1624]" captionTargetBox="[347,1247,771,1587]" captionTargetId="figure-141@11.[347,1260,1116,1593]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 36-42: Geostiba spinosula nov.sp.: (36) male pronotum, elytra, and abdominal segment III (holotype); (37) head in lateral view; (38-39) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (40) apical lobe of paramere; (41) female sternite VIII; (42) spermatheca. Scale bars: 36: 0.5 mm; 37: 0.2 mm; 38-42: 0.1 mm." pageId="10" pageNumber="787">Fig. 37</figureCitation>
), smaller than antennomere III in cross-section, without pigmentation and without ommatidia. Antennae distinctly incrassate apically; antennomeres V-X 2.0-2.5 times as wide as long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB23F60DC67FFE3F56236AFFDCDF892" blockId="10.[347,1255,1728,1809]" pageId="10" pageNumber="787">
Pronotum small, 1.05-1.10 times as wide as head and 1.05-1.10 times as wide as long (
<figureCitation id="133623E5DC67FFE3F55A36B3FE20F970" box="[355,432,1757,1779]" captionStart="Figs 36-42" captionStartId="11.[347,387,1604,1624]" captionTargetBox="[347,1247,771,1587]" captionTargetId="figure-141@11.[347,1260,1116,1593]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 36-42: Geostiba spinosula nov.sp.: (36) male pronotum, elytra, and abdominal segment III (holotype); (37) head in lateral view; (38-39) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (40) apical lobe of paramere; (41) female sternite VIII; (42) spermatheca. Scale bars: 36: 0.5 mm; 37: 0.2 mm; 38-42: 0.1 mm." pageId="10" pageNumber="787">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
); puncturation extremely fine, barely noticeable; microreticulation slightly more distinct than that of head.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB23F60DC66FFE2F736310BFCA3FEF9" blockId="11.[783,819,357,378]" box="[783,819,357,378]" pageId="11" pageNumber="788">788</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB23F60DC66FFE2F56231DEFB54FD83" blockId="11.[347,1255,432,512]" pageId="11" pageNumber="788">
Elytra approximately as wide as pronotum or slightly wider, and about 0.55 times as long as pronotum (
<figureCitation id="133623E5DC66FFE2F5DE31A3FDA4FE60" box="[487,564,461,483]" captionStart="Figs 36-42" captionStartId="11.[347,387,1604,1624]" captionTargetBox="[347,1247,771,1587]" captionTargetId="figure-141@11.[347,1260,1116,1593]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 36-42: Geostiba spinosula nov.sp.: (36) male pronotum, elytra, and abdominal segment III (holotype); (37) head in lateral view; (38-39) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (40) apical lobe of paramere; (41) female sternite VIII; (42) spermatheca. Scale bars: 36: 0.5 mm; 37: 0.2 mm; 38-42: 0.1 mm." pageId="11" pageNumber="788">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
); puncturation very fine, but slightly more distinct than that of head and pronotum; microreticulation shallow; sexual dimorphism moderately pronounced.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB23F60DC66FFE2F5623261FD63FDE3" blockId="11.[347,1255,527,608]" pageId="11" pageNumber="788">Abdomen 1.05-1.10 times as wide as elytra; puncturation very fine and sparse; microreticulation very shallow; posterior margin of tergite VII without palisade fringe; posterior margin of tergite VIII distinctly convex.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB23F60DC66FFE2F549321EFBCEFD79" blockId="11.[347,1255,623,762]" pageId="11" pageNumber="788">
: elytra with lateral margins sharply edged; abdominal tergite III with pronounced smooth median tubercle (
<figureCitation id="133623E5DC66FFE2F65E32E3FD27FD20" box="[615,695,653,675]" captionStart="Figs 36-42" captionStartId="11.[347,387,1604,1624]" captionTargetBox="[347,1247,771,1587]" captionTargetId="figure-141@11.[347,1260,1116,1593]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 36-42: Geostiba spinosula nov.sp.: (36) male pronotum, elytra, and abdominal segment III (holotype); (37) head in lateral view; (38-39) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (40) apical lobe of paramere; (41) female sternite VIII; (42) spermatheca. Scale bars: 36: 0.5 mm; 37: 0.2 mm; 38-42: 0.1 mm." pageId="11" pageNumber="788">Fig. 36</figureCitation>
); tergite VII with small spine-like median process at posterior margin, this process flattened dorso-ventrally and of somewhat triangular shape in antero-dorsal view; posterior margin of sternite VIII strongly convex; median lobe of aedeagus shaped as in 
<figureCitation id="133623E5DC66FFE2F678328AFD20FD79" box="[577,688,740,762]" captionStart="Figs 36-42" captionStartId="11.[347,387,1604,1624]" captionTargetBox="[347,1247,771,1587]" captionTargetId="figure-141@11.[347,1260,1116,1593]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 36-42: Geostiba spinosula nov.sp.: (36) male pronotum, elytra, and abdominal segment III (holotype); (37) head in lateral view; (38-39) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (40) apical lobe of paramere; (41) female sternite VIII; (42) spermatheca. Scale bars: 36: 0.5 mm; 37: 0.2 mm; 38-42: 0.1 mm." pageId="11" pageNumber="788">Figs 38-39</figureCitation>
; apical lobe of paramere slender (
<figureCitation id="133623E5DC66FFE2F03F328AFBC3FD79" box="[1030,1107,740,762]" captionStart="Figs 36-42" captionStartId="11.[347,387,1604,1624]" captionTargetBox="[347,1247,771,1587]" captionTargetId="figure-141@11.[347,1260,1116,1593]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs 36-42: Geostiba spinosula nov.sp.: (36) male pronotum, elytra, and abdominal segment III (holotype); (37) head in lateral view; (38-39) median lobe of aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; (40) apical lobe of paramere; (41) female sternite VIII; (42) spermatheca. Scale bars: 36: 0.5 mm; 37: 0.2 mm; 38-42: 0.1 mm." pageId="11" pageNumber="788">Fig. 40</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF726FE8DC66FFE2F562362AFD3EF91F" pageId="11" pageNumber="788" startId="11.[347,387,1604,1624]" targetBox="[347,1247,771,1587]" targetPageId="11">
<paragraph id="8BB23F60DC66FFE2F562362AFD3EF91F" blockId="11.[347,1255,1604,1692]" pageId="11" pageNumber="788">
<emphasis id="B979E372DC66FFE2F562362AFE51F9DB" bold="true" box="[347,449,1604,1624]" pageId="11" pageNumber="788">Figs 36-42</emphasis>
